","pos":[7382,7467]},{"pos":[7474,7547],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">![</bpt>Screenshot: Table z&amp;#45;order<ept id=\"p1\">]</ept><bpt id=\"p2\">(./media/table-zorder.png \"</bpt>Table_ZOrder<ept id=\"p2\">\")</ept>","source":"![Screenshot: Table z&#45;order](./media/table-zorder.png \"Table_ZOrder\")"},{"pos":[7600,7624],"content":"Spanning Rows or Columns","linkify":"Spanning Rows or Columns","nodes":[{"content":"Spanning Rows or Columns","pos":[0,24]}]},{"pos":[7628,7841],"content":"Table cells may be configured to span multiple rows or columns by using the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.RowSpan%2A&gt;</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.ColumnSpan%2A&gt;</ph> attributes, respectively.","source":"Table cells may be configured to span multiple rows or columns by using the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.RowSpan%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.ColumnSpan%2A> attributes, respectively."},{"content":"Consider the following example, in which a cell spans three columns.","pos":[7848,7916]},{"content":"The following figure shows how this example renders.","pos":[8072,8124]},{"pos":[8131,8226],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">![</bpt>Screenshot: Cell spanning all three columns<ept id=\"p1\">]</ept><bpt id=\"p2\">(./media/table-columnspan.png \"</bpt>Table_ColumnSpan<ept id=\"p2\">\")</ept>","source":"![Screenshot: Cell spanning all three columns](./media/table-columnspan.png \"Table_ColumnSpan\")"},{"pos":[8280,8306],"content":"Building a Table With Code","linkify":"Building a Table With Code","nodes":[{"content":"Building a Table With Code","pos":[0,26]}]},{"content":"The following examples show how to programmatically create a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table&gt;</ph> and populate it with content.","pos":[8310,8438],"source":"The following examples show how to programmatically create a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table> and populate it with content."},{"content":"The contents of the table are apportioned into five rows (represented by <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRow&gt;</ph> objects contained in a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.RowGroups%2A&gt;</ph> object) and six columns (represented by <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableColumn&gt;</ph> objects).","pos":[8439,8720],"source":" The contents of the table are apportioned into five rows (represented by <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRow> objects contained in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.RowGroups%2A> object) and six columns (represented by <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableColumn> objects)."},{"content":"The rows are used for different presentation purposes, including a title row intended to title the entire table, a header row to describe the columns of data in the table, and a footer row with summary information.","pos":[8721,8935]},{"content":"Note that the notion of \"title\", \"header\", and \"footer\" rows are not inherent to the table; these are simply rows with different characteristics.","pos":[8937,9082]},{"content":"Table cells contain the actual content, which can be comprised of text, images, or nearly any other <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_ui](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-ui-md.md)]</ph> element.","pos":[9083,9257],"source":" Table cells contain the actual content, which can be comprised of text, images, or nearly any other [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_ui](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-ui-md.md)] element."},{"pos":[9264,9517],"content":"First, a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.FlowDocument&gt;</ph> is created to host the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table&gt;</ph>, and a new <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table&gt;</ph> is created and added to the contents of the <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.FlowDocument&gt;</ph>.","source":"First, a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.FlowDocument> is created to host the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table>, and a new <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table> is created and added to the contents of the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.FlowDocument>."},{"pos":[9795,9984],"content":"Next, six <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableColumn&gt;</ph> objects are created and added to the table's <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.Columns%2A&gt;</ph> collection, with some formatting applied.","source":"Next, six <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableColumn> objects are created and added to the table's <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.Columns%2A> collection, with some formatting applied."},{"pos":[9992,10119],"content":"[!NOTE]\n Note that the table's <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.Columns%2A> collection uses standard zero-based indexing.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"Note that the table's <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.Columns%2A&gt;</ph> collection uses standard zero-based indexing.","pos":[9,125],"source":"Note that the table's <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.Columns%2A> collection uses standard zero-based indexing."}]},{"content":"Next, a title row is created and added to the table with some formatting applied.","pos":[10425,10506]},{"content":"The title row happens to contain a single cell that spans all six columns in the table.","pos":[10508,10595]},{"content":"Next, a header row is created and added to the table, and the cells in the header row are created and populated with content.","pos":[10893,11018]},{"content":"Next, a row for data is created and added to the table, and the cells in this row are created and populated with content.","pos":[11320,11441]},{"content":"Building this row is similar to building the header row, with slightly different formatting applied.","pos":[11443,11543]},{"content":"Finally, a footer row is created, added, and formatted.","pos":[11837,11892]},{"content":"Like the title row, the footer contains a single cell that spans all six colu